  "explanation": "The defendant has been found guilty of embezzling $25,000, which represents a significant breach of fiduciary duty and trust toward their employer. However, several mitigating factors must be considered during sentencing. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating that this behavior is entirely out of character and suggesting a high likelihood of successful rehabilitation. Furthermore, the defendant has already begun to make partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. While incarceration is necessary to serve as a deterrent and acknowledge the severity of white-collar theft, a lengthy prison term would hinder the defendant's ability to earn an income and complete the restitution payments. Therefore, a brief period of incarceration, followed by a probationary period focused on repaying the remaining stolen funds, is the most appropriate and balanced sentence.",
